'''''The Bloom and the Blight''''' is the fourth full-length album from the band [[Two Gallants (band)|Two Gallants]], released on September 4, 2012. It follows up their self-titled album, ''[[Two Gallants (album)|Two Gallants]]'', which was released on September 25, 2007. A streaming version of the full album was made available on August 27, 2012, by ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine.\n\n==Track listing==\n# \"Halcyon Days\"\n# \"Song of Songs\"\n# \"My Love Won't Wait\"\n# \"Broken Eyes\"\n# \"Ride Away\"\n# \"Decay\"\n# \"Winter's Youth\"\n# \"Willie\"\n# \"Cradle Pyre\"\n# \"Sunday Souvenirs\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Two Gallants}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bloom and the Blight, The}}\n\n[[Category:2012 albums]]\n[[Category:Two Gallants (band) albums]]\n[[Category:ATO Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by John Congleton]]\n\n{{2010s-indie-rock-album-stub}}\n\n[[gl:Two Gallants (\u00e1lbum)]]\n", "name_user": "Caro7200", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Bloom_and_the_Blight"}
